:R-HSA-392851  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Prostacyclin (PGI2) is continuously produced by healthy vascular endothelial cells. It inhibits platelet activation through interaction with the Gs-coupled receptor PTGIR, leading to increased cAMP, a consequent increase in cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity which prevents increases of cytoplasmic [Ca2+] necessary for activation (Woulfe et al. 2001). PGI2 is also an effective vasodilator. These effects oppose the effects of thromboxane (TXA2), another eicosanoid, creating a balance of blood circulation and platelet activation." ;
        rdfs:label          "Prostacyclin signalling through prostacyclin receptor" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Akkerman, JW, 2009-06-03" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Kunapuli, SP, 2010-06-07" , "Edited: Jupe, S, 2010-06-07" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-392851" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-418346/R-HSA-418346> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

